37gl::ImageIndex GetZeroLevelIndex(const mtl::TextureRef &image)
38{
39 switch (image->textureType())
40 {
41 case MTLTextureType2D:
42 return gl::ImageIndex::Make2D(0);
43 case MTLTextureTypeCube:
44 return gl::ImageIndex::MakeFromType(gl::TextureType::CubeMap, 0);
45 case MTLTextureType2DArray:
46 return gl::ImageIndex::Make2DArray(0 /** entire layers */);
47 case MTLTextureType2DMultisample:
48 return gl::ImageIndex::Make2DMultisample();
49 case MTLTextureType3D:
50 return gl::ImageIndex::Make3D(0 /** entire layers */);
51 default:
52 UNREACHABLE();
53 break;
54 }
55
56 return gl::ImageIndex();
57}
58
59// Slice is ignored if texture type is not Cube or 2D array
60gl::ImageIndex GetCubeOrArraySliceMipIndex(const mtl::TextureRef &image,
61 uint32_t slice,
62 uint32_t level)
63{
64 switch (image->textureType())
65 {
66 case MTLTextureType2D:
67 return gl::ImageIndex::Make2D(level);
68 case MTLTextureTypeCube:
69 {
70 auto cubeFace = static_cast<gl::TextureTarget>(
71 static_cast<int>(gl::TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveX) + slice);
72 return gl::ImageIndex::MakeCubeMapFace(cubeFace, level);
73 }
74 case MTLTextureType2DArray:
75 return gl::ImageIndex::Make2DArray(level, slice);
76 case MTLTextureType2DMultisample:
77 return gl::ImageIndex::Make2DMultisample();
78 case MTLTextureType3D:
79 return gl::ImageIndex::Make3D(level);
80 default:
81 UNREACHABLE();
82 break;
83 }
84
85 return gl::ImageIndex();
86}
87
88// layer is ignored if texture type is not Cube or 2D array or 3D
89gl::ImageIndex GetLayerMipIndex(const mtl::TextureRef &image, uint32_t layer, uint32_t level)
90{
91 switch (image->textureType())
92 {
93 case MTLTextureType2D:
94 return gl::ImageIndex::Make2D(level);
95 case MTLTextureTypeCube:
96 {
97 auto cubeFace = static_cast<gl::TextureTarget>(
98 static_cast<int>(gl::TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveX) + layer);
99 return gl::ImageIndex::MakeCubeMapFace(cubeFace, level);
100 }
101 case MTLTextureType2DArray:
102 return gl::ImageIndex::Make2DArray(level, layer);
103 case MTLTextureType2DMultisample:
104 return gl::ImageIndex::Make2DMultisample();
105 case MTLTextureType3D:
106 return gl::ImageIndex::Make3D(level, layer);
107 default:
108 UNREACHABLE();
109 break;
110 }
111
112 return gl::ImageIndex();
113}

115GLuint GetImageLayerIndexFrom(const gl::ImageIndex &index)
116{
117 switch (index.getType())
118 {
119 case gl::TextureType::_2D:
120 case gl::TextureType::_2DMultisample:
121 case gl::TextureType::Rectangle:
122 return 0;
123 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
124 return index.cubeMapFaceIndex();
125 case gl::TextureType::_2DArray:
126 case gl::TextureType::_3D:
127 return index.getLayerIndex();
128 default:
129 UNREACHABLE();
130 }
131
132 return 0;
133}
134
135GLuint GetImageCubeFaceIndexOrZeroFrom(const gl::ImageIndex &index)
136{
137 switch (index.getType())
138 {
139 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
140 return index.cubeMapFaceIndex();
141 default:
142 break;
143 }
144
145 return 0;
146}

148// Given texture type, get texture type of one image for a glTexImage call.
149// For example, for texture 2d, one image is also texture 2d.
150// for texture cube, one image is texture 2d.
151gl::TextureType GetTextureImageType(gl::TextureType texType)
152{
153 switch (texType)
154 {
155 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
156 return gl::TextureType::_2D;
157 case gl::TextureType::_2D:
158 case gl::TextureType::_2DArray:
159 case gl::TextureType::_2DMultisample:
160 case gl::TextureType::_3D:
161 case gl::TextureType::Rectangle:
162 return texType;
163 default:
164 UNREACHABLE();
165 return gl::TextureType::InvalidEnum;
166 }
167}

169// D24X8 by default writes depth data to high 24 bits of 32 bit integers. However, Metal separate
170// depth stencil blitting expects depth data to be in low 24 bits of the data.
171void WriteDepthStencilToDepth24(const uint8_t *srcPtr, uint8_t *dstPtr)
172{
173 auto src = reinterpret_cast<const angle::DepthStencil *>(srcPtr);
174 auto dst = reinterpret_cast<uint32_t *>(dstPtr);
175 *dst = gl::floatToNormalized<24, uint32_t>(static_cast<float>(src->depth));
176}

179#if TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR
180void CopyTextureData(const MTLSize &regionSize,
181 size_t srcRowPitch,
182 size_t src2DImageSize,
183 const uint8_t *psrc,
184 size_t destRowPitch,
185 size_t dest2DImageSize,
186 uint8_t *pdst)
187{
188 {
189 size_t rowCopySize = std::min(srcRowPitch, destRowPitch);
190 for (NSUInteger d = 0; d < regionSize.depth; ++d)
191 {
192 for (NSUInteger r = 0; r < regionSize.height; ++r)
193 {
194 const uint8_t *pCopySrc = psrc + d * src2DImageSize + r * srcRowPitch;
195 uint8_t *pCopyDst = pdst + d * dest2DImageSize + r * destRowPitch;
196 memcpy(pCopyDst, pCopySrc, rowCopySize);
197 }
198 }
199 }
200}
201#endif // TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR
202
203void ConvertDepthStencilData(const MTLSize &regionSize,
204 const angle::Format &srcAngleFormat,
205 size_t srcRowPitch,
206 size_t src2DImageSize,
207 const uint8_t *psrc,
208 const angle::Format &dstAngleFormat,
209 rx::PixelWriteFunction pixelWriteFunctionOverride,
210 size_t destRowPitch,
211 size_t dest2DImageSize,
212 uint8_t *pdst)
213{
214 if (srcAngleFormat.id == dstAngleFormat.id)
215 {
216 size_t rowCopySize = std::min(srcRowPitch, destRowPitch);
217 for (NSUInteger d = 0; d < regionSize.depth; ++d)
218 {
219 for (NSUInteger r = 0; r < regionSize.height; ++r)
220 {
221 const uint8_t *pCopySrc = psrc + d * src2DImageSize + r * srcRowPitch;
222 uint8_t *pCopyDst = pdst + d * dest2DImageSize + r * destRowPitch;
223 memcpy(pCopyDst, pCopySrc, rowCopySize);
224 }
225 }
226 }
227 else
228 {
229 rx::PixelWriteFunction pixelWriteFunction = pixelWriteFunctionOverride
230 ? pixelWriteFunctionOverride
231 : dstAngleFormat.pixelWriteFunction;
232 // This is only for depth & stencil case.
233 ASSERT(srcAngleFormat.depthBits || srcAngleFormat.stencilBits);
234 ASSERT(srcAngleFormat.pixelReadFunction && pixelWriteFunction);
235
236 // cache to store read result of source pixel
237 angle::DepthStencil depthStencilData;
238 auto sourcePixelReadData = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t *>(&depthStencilData);
239 ASSERT(srcAngleFormat.pixelBytes <= sizeof(depthStencilData));
240
241 for (NSUInteger d = 0; d < regionSize.depth; ++d)
242 {
243 for (NSUInteger r = 0; r < regionSize.height; ++r)
244 {
245 for (NSUInteger c = 0; c < regionSize.width; ++c)
246 {
247 const uint8_t *sourcePixelData =
248 psrc + d * src2DImageSize + r * srcRowPitch + c * srcAngleFormat.pixelBytes;
249
250 uint8_t *destPixelData = pdst + d * dest2DImageSize + r * destRowPitch +
251 c * dstAngleFormat.pixelBytes;
252
253 srcAngleFormat.pixelReadFunction(sourcePixelData, sourcePixelReadData);
254 pixelWriteFunction(sourcePixelReadData, destPixelData);
255 }
256 }
257 }
258 }
259}

261angle::Result CopyDepthStencilTextureContentsToStagingBuffer(
262 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
263 const angle::Format &textureAngleFormat,
264 const angle::Format &stagingAngleFormat,
265 rx::PixelWriteFunction pixelWriteFunctionOverride,
266 const MTLSize &regionSize,
267 const uint8_t *data,
268 size_t bytesPerRow,
269 size_t bytesPer2DImage,
270 size_t *bufferRowPitchOut,
271 size_t *buffer2DImageSizeOut,
272 mtl::BufferRef *bufferOut)
273{
274 size_t stagingBufferRowPitch = regionSize.width * stagingAngleFormat.pixelBytes;
275 size_t stagingBuffer2DImageSize = stagingBufferRowPitch * regionSize.height;
276 size_t stagingBufferSize = stagingBuffer2DImageSize * regionSize.depth;
277 mtl::BufferRef stagingBuffer;
278 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::Buffer::MakeBuffer(contextMtl, stagingBufferSize, nullptr, &stagingBuffer));
279
280 uint8_t *pdst = stagingBuffer->map(contextMtl);
281
282 ConvertDepthStencilData(regionSize, textureAngleFormat, bytesPerRow, bytesPer2DImage, data,
283 stagingAngleFormat, pixelWriteFunctionOverride, stagingBufferRowPitch,
284 stagingBuffer2DImageSize, pdst);
285
286 stagingBuffer->unmap(contextMtl);
287
288 *bufferOut = stagingBuffer;
289 *bufferRowPitchOut = stagingBufferRowPitch;
290 *buffer2DImageSizeOut = stagingBuffer2DImageSize;
291
292 return angle::Result::Continue;
293}

326angle::Result CopyCompressedTextureContentsToStagingBuffer(
327 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
328 const angle::Format &textureAngleFormat,
329 const MTLSize &regionSizeInBlocks,
330 const uint8_t *data,
331 size_t bytesPerBlockRow,
332 size_t bytesPer2DImage,
333 size_t *bufferRowPitchOut,
334 size_t *buffer2DImageSizeOut,
335 mtl::BufferRef *bufferOut)
336{
337 size_t stagingBufferRowPitch = bytesPerBlockRow;
338 size_t stagingBuffer2DImageSize = bytesPer2DImage;
339 size_t stagingBufferSize = stagingBuffer2DImageSize * regionSizeInBlocks.depth;
340 mtl::BufferRef stagingBuffer;
341 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::Buffer::MakeBuffer(contextMtl, stagingBufferSize, nullptr, &stagingBuffer));
342
343 uint8_t *pdst = stagingBuffer->map(contextMtl);
344 CopyTextureData(regionSizeInBlocks, bytesPerBlockRow, bytesPer2DImage,
345 data, stagingBufferRowPitch, stagingBuffer2DImageSize, pdst);
346
347 stagingBuffer->unmap(contextMtl);
348
349 *bufferOut = stagingBuffer;
350 *bufferRowPitchOut = stagingBufferRowPitch;
351 *buffer2DImageSizeOut = stagingBuffer2DImageSize;
352
353 return angle::Result::Continue;

357angle::Result UploadDepthStencilTextureContentsWithStagingBuffer(
358 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
359 const angle::Format &textureAngleFormat,
360 MTLRegion region,
361 const mtl::MipmapNativeLevel &mipmapLevel,
362 uint32_t slice,
363 const uint8_t *data,
364 size_t bytesPerRow,
365 size_t bytesPer2DImage,
366 const mtl::TextureRef &texture)
367{
368 ASSERT(texture && texture->valid());
369
370 ASSERT(!texture->isCPUAccessible());
371
372 ASSERT(!textureAngleFormat.depthBits || !textureAngleFormat.stencilBits);
373
374 // Compressed texture is not supporte atm
375 ASSERT(!textureAngleFormat.isBlock);
376
377 // Copy data to staging buffer
378 size_t stagingBufferRowPitch;
379 size_t stagingBuffer2DImageSize;
380 mtl::BufferRef stagingBuffer;
381 ANGLE_TRY(CopyDepthStencilTextureContentsToStagingBuffer(
382 contextMtl, textureAngleFormat, textureAngleFormat, textureAngleFormat.pixelWriteFunction,
383 region.size, data, bytesPerRow, bytesPer2DImage, &stagingBufferRowPitch,
384 &stagingBuffer2DImageSize, &stagingBuffer));
385
386 // Copy staging buffer to texture.
387 mtl::BlitCommandEncoder *encoder = contextMtl->getBlitCommandEncoder();
388 encoder->copyBufferToTexture(stagingBuffer, 0, stagingBufferRowPitch, stagingBuffer2DImageSize,
389 region.size, texture, slice, mipmapLevel, region.origin,
390 MTLBlitOptionNone);
391
392 return angle::Result::Continue;
393}
394
395// Packed depth stencil upload using staging buffer
396angle::Result UploadPackedDepthStencilTextureContentsWithStagingBuffer(
397 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
398 const angle::Format &textureAngleFormat,
399 MTLRegion region,
400 const mtl::MipmapNativeLevel &mipmapLevel,
401 uint32_t slice,
402 const uint8_t *data,
403 size_t bytesPerRow,
404 size_t bytesPer2DImage,
405 const mtl::TextureRef &texture)
406{
407 ASSERT(texture && texture->valid());
408
409 ASSERT(!texture->isCPUAccessible());
410
411 ASSERT(textureAngleFormat.depthBits && textureAngleFormat.stencilBits);
412
413 // We have to split the depth & stencil data into 2 buffers.
414 angle::FormatID stagingDepthBufferFormatId;
415 angle::FormatID stagingStencilBufferFormatId;
416 // Custom depth write function. We cannot use those in imageformats.cpp since Metal has some
417 // special cases.
418 rx::PixelWriteFunction stagingDepthBufferWriteFunctionOverride = nullptr;
419
420 switch (textureAngleFormat.id)
421 {
422 case angle::FormatID::D24_UNORM_S8_UINT:
423 // D24_UNORM_X8_UINT writes depth data to high 24 bits. But Metal expects depth data to
424 // be in low 24 bits.
425 stagingDepthBufferFormatId = angle::FormatID::D24_UNORM_X8_UINT;
426 stagingDepthBufferWriteFunctionOverride = WriteDepthStencilToDepth24;
427 stagingStencilBufferFormatId = angle::FormatID::S8_UINT;
428 break;
429 case angle::FormatID::D32_FLOAT_S8X24_UINT:
430 stagingDepthBufferFormatId = angle::FormatID::D32_FLOAT;
431 stagingStencilBufferFormatId = angle::FormatID::S8_UINT;
432 break;
433 default:
434 ANGLE_MTL_UNREACHABLE(contextMtl);
435 }
436
437 const angle::Format &angleStagingDepthFormat = angle::Format::Get(stagingDepthBufferFormatId);
438 const angle::Format &angleStagingStencilFormat =
439 angle::Format::Get(stagingStencilBufferFormatId);
440
441 size_t stagingDepthBufferRowPitch, stagingStencilBufferRowPitch;
442 size_t stagingDepthBuffer2DImageSize, stagingStencilBuffer2DImageSize;
443 mtl::BufferRef stagingDepthbuffer, stagingStencilBuffer;
444
445 // Copy depth data to staging depth buffer
446 ANGLE_TRY(CopyDepthStencilTextureContentsToStagingBuffer(
447 contextMtl, textureAngleFormat, angleStagingDepthFormat,
448 stagingDepthBufferWriteFunctionOverride, region.size, data, bytesPerRow, bytesPer2DImage,
449 &stagingDepthBufferRowPitch, &stagingDepthBuffer2DImageSize, &stagingDepthbuffer));
450
451 // Copy stencil data to staging stencil buffer
452 ANGLE_TRY(CopyDepthStencilTextureContentsToStagingBuffer(
453 contextMtl, textureAngleFormat, angleStagingStencilFormat, nullptr, region.size, data,
454 bytesPerRow, bytesPer2DImage, &stagingStencilBufferRowPitch,
455 &stagingStencilBuffer2DImageSize, &stagingStencilBuffer));
456
457 mtl::BlitCommandEncoder *encoder = contextMtl->getBlitCommandEncoder();
458
459 encoder->copyBufferToTexture(stagingDepthbuffer, 0, stagingDepthBufferRowPitch,
460 stagingDepthBuffer2DImageSize, region.size, texture, slice,
461 mipmapLevel, region.origin, MTLBlitOptionDepthFromDepthStencil);
462 encoder->copyBufferToTexture(stagingStencilBuffer, 0, stagingStencilBufferRowPitch,
463 stagingStencilBuffer2DImageSize, region.size, texture, slice,
464 mipmapLevel, region.origin, MTLBlitOptionStencilFromDepthStencil);
465
466 return angle::Result::Continue;
467}
468
469#if TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR
470angle::Result UploadTextureContentsWithStagingBuffer(
471 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
472 const angle::Format &textureAngleFormat,
473 MTLRegion region,
474 const mtl::MipmapNativeLevel &mipmapLevel,
475 uint32_t slice,
476 const uint8_t *data,
477 size_t bytesPerRow,
478 size_t bytesPer2DImage,
479 const mtl::TextureRef &texture)
480{
481 ASSERT(texture && texture->valid());
482
483 angle::FormatID stagingBufferFormatID = textureAngleFormat.id;
484 const angle::Format &angleStagingFormat = angle::Format::Get(stagingBufferFormatID);
485
486
487 size_t stagingBufferRowPitch;
488 size_t stagingBuffer2DImageSize;
489 mtl::BufferRef stagingBuffer;
490
491 // Block-compressed formats need a bit of massaging for copy.
492 if(textureAngleFormat.isBlock)
493 {
494 GLenum internalFormat = textureAngleFormat.glInternalFormat;
495 const gl::InternalFormat & fmt = gl::GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat);
496 MTLRegion newRegion = region;
497 bytesPerRow = (region.size.width + fmt.compressedBlockWidth -1 )/ fmt.compressedBlockWidth * 16;
498 bytesPer2DImage = (region.size.height + fmt.compressedBlockHeight -1 ) / fmt.compressedBlockHeight * bytesPerRow;
499 newRegion.size.width = (region.size.width + fmt.compressedBlockWidth -1 ) / fmt.compressedBlockWidth;
500 newRegion.size.height = (region.size.height + fmt.compressedBlockHeight -1 ) / fmt.compressedBlockHeight;
501 ANGLE_TRY(CopyCompressedTextureContentsToStagingBuffer(contextMtl, angleStagingFormat, newRegion.size, data, bytesPerRow, bytesPer2DImage, &stagingBufferRowPitch, &stagingBuffer2DImageSize, &stagingBuffer));
502 }
503 //Copy to staging buffer before uploading to texture.
504 else
505 {
506 ANGLE_TRY(CopyTextureContentsToStagingBuffer(contextMtl, angleStagingFormat, region.size, data, bytesPerRow, bytesPer2DImage, &stagingBufferRowPitch, &stagingBuffer2DImageSize, &stagingBuffer));
507 }
508 mtl::BlitCommandEncoder *encoder = contextMtl->getBlitCommandEncoder();
509
510 encoder->copyBufferToTexture(stagingBuffer, 0, stagingBufferRowPitch,
511 stagingBuffer2DImageSize, region.size, texture, slice,
512 mipmapLevel, region.origin, 0);
513
514
515 return angle::Result::Continue;
516}
517#endif //TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR
518
519angle::Result UploadTextureContents(const gl::Context *context,
520 const angle::Format &textureAngleFormat,
521 const MTLRegion &region,
522 const mtl::MipmapNativeLevel &mipmapLevel,
523 uint32_t slice,
524 const uint8_t *data,
525 size_t bytesPerRow,
526 size_t bytesPer2DImage,
527 const mtl::TextureRef &texture)
528{
529 ASSERT(texture && texture->valid());
530 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
531#if TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR
532 if (!textureAngleFormat.depthBits && !textureAngleFormat.stencilBits)
533 {
534 ANGLE_TRY(UploadTextureContentsWithStagingBuffer(contextMtl,textureAngleFormat,region,mipmapLevel,slice,data,bytesPerRow,bytesPer2DImage,texture));
535 return angle::Result::Continue;
536 }
537#else
538 if (texture->isCPUAccessible())
539 {
540 // If texture is CPU accessible, just call replaceRegion() directly.
541 texture->replaceRegion(contextMtl, region, mipmapLevel, slice, data, bytesPerRow,
542 bytesPer2DImage);
543
544 return angle::Result::Continue;
545 }
546#endif // TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR
547 ASSERT(textureAngleFormat.depthBits || textureAngleFormat.stencilBits);
548
549 // Texture is not CPU accessible, we need to use staging buffer
550 if (textureAngleFormat.depthBits && textureAngleFormat.stencilBits)
551 {
552 ANGLE_TRY(UploadPackedDepthStencilTextureContentsWithStagingBuffer(
553 contextMtl, textureAngleFormat, region, mipmapLevel, slice, data, bytesPerRow,
554 bytesPer2DImage, texture));
555 }
556 else
557 {
558 ANGLE_TRY(UploadDepthStencilTextureContentsWithStagingBuffer(
559 contextMtl, textureAngleFormat, region, mipmapLevel, slice, data, bytesPerRow,
560 bytesPer2DImage, texture));
561 }
562
563 return angle::Result::Continue;
564}

566// This might be unused on platform not supporting swizzle.
567ANGLE_MTL_UNUSED
568GLenum OverrideSwizzleValue(const gl::Context *context,
569 GLenum swizzle,
570 const mtl::Format &format,
571 const gl::InternalFormat &glInternalFormat)
572{
573 if (format.actualAngleFormat().depthBits)
574 {
575 ASSERT(!format.swizzled);
576 if (context->getState().getClientMajorVersion() >= 3 && glInternalFormat.sized)
577 {
578 // ES 3.0 spec: treat depth texture as red texture during sampling.
579 if (swizzle == GL_GREEN || swizzle == GL_BLUE)
580 {
581 return GL_NONE;
582 }
583 else if (swizzle == GL_ALPHA)
584 {
585 return GL_ONE;
586 }
587 }
588 else
589 {
590 // https://www.khronos.org/registry/OpenGL/extensions/OES/OES_depth_texture.txt
591 // Treat depth texture as luminance texture during sampling.
592 if (swizzle == GL_GREEN || swizzle == GL_BLUE)
593 {
594 return GL_RED;
595 }
596 else if (swizzle == GL_ALPHA)
597 {
598 return GL_ONE;
599 }
600 }
601 }
602 else if (format.swizzled)
603 {
604 // Combine the swizzles
605 switch (swizzle)
606 {
607 case GL_RED:
608 return format.swizzle[0];
609 case GL_GREEN:
610 return format.swizzle[1];
611 case GL_BLUE:
612 return format.swizzle[2];
613 case GL_ALPHA:
614 return format.swizzle[3];
615 default:
616 break;
617 }
618 }
619
620 return swizzle;
621}

635void TextureMtl::releaseTexture(bool releaseImages)
636{
637 releaseTexture(releaseImages, false);
638}
639
640void TextureMtl::releaseTexture(bool releaseImages, bool releaseTextureObjectsOnly)
641{
642
643 if (releaseImages)
644 {
645 mTexImageDefs.clear();
646 }
647 else if (mNativeTexture)
648 {
649 // Release native texture but keep its old per face per mipmap level image views.
650 retainImageDefinitions();
651 }
652
653 mNativeTexture = nullptr;
654 mNativeSwizzleSamplingView = nullptr;
655
656 // Clear render target cache for each texture's image. We don't erase them because they
657 // might still be referenced by a framebuffer.
658 for (auto &sliceRenderTargets : mPerLayerRenderTargets)
659 {
660 for (RenderTargetMtl &mipRenderTarget : sliceRenderTargets.second)
661 {
662 mipRenderTarget.reset();
663 }
664 }
665
666 for (mtl::TextureRef &view : mNativeLevelViews)
667 {
668 view.reset();
669 }
670
671 if (!releaseTextureObjectsOnly)
672 {
673 mMetalSamplerState = nil;
674 mFormat = mtl::Format();
675 mIsPow2 = false;
676 }
677}
678
679angle::Result TextureMtl::ensureTextureCreated(const gl::Context *context)
680{
681 if (mNativeTexture)
682 {
683 return angle::Result::Continue;
684 }
685
686 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
687
688 // Create actual texture object:
689 mCurrentBaseLevel = mState.getEffectiveBaseLevel();
690
691 const GLuint mips = mState.getMipmapMaxLevel() - mCurrentBaseLevel + 1;
692 gl::ImageDesc desc = mState.getBaseLevelDesc();
693 ANGLE_MTL_CHECK(contextMtl, desc.format.valid(), GL_INVALID_OPERATION);
694 angle::FormatID angleFormatId =
695 angle::Format::InternalFormatToID(desc.format.info->sizedInternalFormat);
696 mFormat = contextMtl->getPixelFormat(angleFormatId);
697
698 return createNativeTexture(context, mState.getType(), mips, desc.size);
699}
700
701angle::Result TextureMtl::createNativeTexture(const gl::Context *context,
702 gl::TextureType type,
703 GLuint mips,
704 const gl::Extents &size)
705{
706 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
707
708 // Create actual texture object:
709 mCurrentBaseLevel = mState.getEffectiveBaseLevel();
710 mCurrentMaxLevel = mState.getEffectiveMaxLevel();
711
712 mIsPow2 = gl::isPow2(size.width) && gl::isPow2(size.height) && gl::isPow2(size.depth);
713 mSlices = 1;
714 int numCubeFaces = 1;
715 switch (type)
716 {
717 case gl::TextureType::_2D:
718 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::Texture::Make2DTexture(
719 contextMtl, mFormat, size.width, size.height, mips,
720 /** renderTargetOnly */ false,
721 /** allowFormatView */ mFormat.hasDepthAndStencilBits(), &mNativeTexture));
722 break;
723 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
724 mSlices = numCubeFaces = 6;
725 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::Texture::MakeCubeTexture(
726 contextMtl, mFormat, size.width, mips,
727 /** renderTargetOnly */ false,
728 /** allowFormatView */ mFormat.hasDepthAndStencilBits(), &mNativeTexture));
729 break;
730 case gl::TextureType::_3D:
731 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::Texture::Make3DTexture(
732 contextMtl, mFormat, size.width, size.height, size.depth, mips,
733 /** renderTargetOnly */ false,
734 /** allowFormatView */ mFormat.hasDepthAndStencilBits(), &mNativeTexture));
735 break;
736 case gl::TextureType::_2DArray:
737 mSlices = size.depth;
738 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::Texture::Make2DArrayTexture(
739 contextMtl, mFormat, size.width, size.height, mips, mSlices,
740 /** renderTargetOnly */ false,
741 /** allowFormatView */ mFormat.hasDepthAndStencilBits(), &mNativeTexture));
742 break;
743 default:
744 UNREACHABLE();
745 }
746
747 ANGLE_TRY(checkForEmulatedChannels(context, mFormat, mNativeTexture));
748
749 // Transfer data from images to actual texture object
750 mtl::BlitCommandEncoder *encoder = nullptr;
751 for (int face = 0; face < numCubeFaces; ++face)
752 {
753 for (mtl::MipmapNativeLevel actualMip = mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel; actualMip.get() < mips;
754 ++actualMip)
755 {
756 GLuint imageMipLevel = mtl::GetGLMipLevel(actualMip, mState.getEffectiveBaseLevel());
757 mtl::TextureRef &imageToTransfer = mTexImageDefs[face][imageMipLevel].image;
758
759 // Only transfer if this mip & slice image has been defined and in correct size &
760 // format.
761 gl::Extents actualMipSize = mNativeTexture->size(actualMip);
762 if (imageToTransfer && imageToTransfer->sizeAt0() == actualMipSize &&
763 imageToTransfer->pixelFormat() == mNativeTexture->pixelFormat())
764 {
765 if (!encoder)
766 {
767 encoder = contextMtl->getBlitCommandEncoder();
768 }
769 encoder->copyTexture(imageToTransfer, 0, mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel, mNativeTexture,
770 face, actualMip, imageToTransfer->arrayLength(), 1);
771
772 // Invalidate texture image definition at this index so that we can make it a
773 // view of the native texture at this index later.
774 imageToTransfer = nullptr;
775 }
776 }
777 }
778
779 // Create sampler state
780 ANGLE_TRY(ensureSamplerStateCreated(context));
781
782 return angle::Result::Continue;
783}
784
785angle::Result TextureMtl::ensureSamplerStateCreated(const gl::Context *context)
786{
787 if (mMetalSamplerState)
788 {
789 return angle::Result::Continue;
790 }
791
792 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
793 DisplayMtl *displayMtl = contextMtl->getDisplay();
794
795 mtl::SamplerDesc samplerDesc(mState.getSamplerState());
796
797 if (mFormat.actualAngleFormat().depthBits &&
798 !displayMtl->getFeatures().hasDepthTextureFiltering.enabled)
799 {
800 // On devices not supporting filtering for depth textures, we need to convert to nearest
801 // here.
802 samplerDesc.minFilter = MTLSamplerMinMagFilterNearest;
803 samplerDesc.magFilter = MTLSamplerMinMagFilterNearest;
804 if (samplerDesc.mipFilter != MTLSamplerMipFilterNotMipmapped)
805 {
806 samplerDesc.mipFilter = MTLSamplerMipFilterNearest;
807 }
808
809 samplerDesc.maxAnisotropy = 1;
810 }
811 if (mState.getType() == gl::TextureType::Rectangle)
812 {
813 samplerDesc.normalizedCoordinates = NO;
814 samplerDesc.rAddressMode = MTLSamplerAddressModeClampToEdge;
815 samplerDesc.sAddressMode = MTLSamplerAddressModeClampToEdge;
816 samplerDesc.tAddressMode = MTLSamplerAddressModeClampToEdge;
817 }
818 else
819 {
820 samplerDesc.normalizedCoordinates = YES;
821 }
822 mMetalSamplerState =
823 displayMtl->getStateCache().getSamplerState(displayMtl->getMetalDevice(), samplerDesc);
824
825 return angle::Result::Continue;
826}
827
828angle::Result TextureMtl::onBaseMaxLevelsChanged(const gl::Context *context)
829{
830 if (!mNativeTexture || (mCurrentBaseLevel == mState.getEffectiveBaseLevel() &&
831 mCurrentMaxLevel == mState.getEffectiveMaxLevel()))
832 {
833 return angle::Result::Continue;
834 }
835
836 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
837
838 // Release native texture but keep old image definitions so that it can be recreated from old
839 // image definitions with different base level
840 releaseTexture(false, true);
841
842 // Tell context to rebind textures
843 contextMtl->invalidateCurrentTextures();
844
845 return angle::Result::Continue;
846}
847
848angle::Result TextureMtl::ensureImageCreated(const gl::Context *context,
849 const gl::ImageIndex &index)
850{
851 mtl::TextureRef &image = getImage(index);
852 if (!image)
853 {
854 // Image at this level hasn't been defined yet. We need to define it:
855 const gl::ImageDesc &desc = mState.getImageDesc(index);
856 ANGLE_TRY(redefineImage(context, index, mFormat, desc.size));
857 }
858 return angle::Result::Continue;
859}
860
861angle::Result TextureMtl::ensureNativeLevelViewsCreated()
862{
863 ASSERT(mNativeTexture);
864 const GLuint baseLevel = mState.getEffectiveBaseLevel();
865 for (mtl::MipmapNativeLevel mip = mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel;
866 mip.get() < mNativeTexture->mipmapLevels(); ++mip)
867 {
868 if (mNativeLevelViews[mip])
869 {
870 continue;
871 }
872
873 if (mNativeTexture->textureType() != MTLTextureTypeCube &&
874 mTexImageDefs[0][mtl::GetGLMipLevel(mip, baseLevel)].image)
875 {
876 // Reuse texture image view.
877 mNativeLevelViews[mip] = mTexImageDefs[0][mtl::GetGLMipLevel(mip, baseLevel)].image;
878 }
879 else
880 {
881 mNativeLevelViews[mip] = mNativeTexture->createMipView(mip);
882 }
883 }
884 return angle::Result::Continue;
885}
886
887mtl::TextureRef TextureMtl::createImageViewFromNativeTexture(
888 GLuint cubeFaceOrZero,
889 const mtl::MipmapNativeLevel &nativeLevel)
890{
891 mtl::TextureRef image;
892 if (mNativeTexture->textureType() == MTLTextureTypeCube)
893 {
894 // Cube texture's image is per face.
895 image = mNativeTexture->createSliceMipView(cubeFaceOrZero, nativeLevel);
896 }
897 else
898 {
899 if (mNativeLevelViews[nativeLevel])
900 {
901 // Reuse the native level view
902 image = mNativeLevelViews[nativeLevel];
903 }
904 else
905 {
906 image = mNativeTexture->createMipView(nativeLevel);
907 }
908 }
909
910 return image;
911}
912
913void TextureMtl::retainImageDefinitions()
914{
915 if (!mNativeTexture)
916 {
917 return;
918 }
919 const GLuint mips = mNativeTexture->mipmapLevels();
920
921 int numCubeFaces = 1;
922 switch (mState.getType())
923 {
924 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
925 numCubeFaces = 6;
926 break;
927 default:
928 break;
929 }
930
931 // Create image view per cube face, per mip level
932 for (int face = 0; face < numCubeFaces; ++face)
933 {
934 for (mtl::MipmapNativeLevel mip = mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel; mip.get() < mips; ++mip)
935 {
936 GLuint imageMipLevel = mtl::GetGLMipLevel(mip, mCurrentBaseLevel);
937 ImageDefinitionMtl &imageDef = mTexImageDefs[face][imageMipLevel];
938 if (imageDef.image)
939 {
940 continue;
941 }
942 imageDef.image = createImageViewFromNativeTexture(face, mip);
943 imageDef.formatID = mFormat.intendedFormatId;
944 }
945 }
946}
947
948bool TextureMtl::isIndexWithinMinMaxLevels(const gl::ImageIndex &imageIndex) const
949{
950 return imageIndex.getLevelIndex() >= static_cast<GLint>(mState.getEffectiveBaseLevel()) &&
951 imageIndex.getLevelIndex() <= static_cast<GLint>(mState.getEffectiveMaxLevel());
952}
953
954mtl::MipmapNativeLevel TextureMtl::getNativeLevel(const gl::ImageIndex &imageIndex) const
955{
956 int baseLevel = mState.getEffectiveBaseLevel();
957 return mtl::GetNativeMipLevel(imageIndex.getLevelIndex(), baseLevel);
958}
959
960mtl::TextureRef &TextureMtl::getImage(const gl::ImageIndex &imageIndex)
961{
962 return getImageDefinition(imageIndex).image;
963}
964
965ImageDefinitionMtl &TextureMtl::getImageDefinition(const gl::ImageIndex &imageIndex)
966{
967 GLuint cubeFaceOrZero = GetImageCubeFaceIndexOrZeroFrom(imageIndex);
968 ImageDefinitionMtl &imageDef = mTexImageDefs[cubeFaceOrZero][imageIndex.getLevelIndex()];
969
970 if (!imageDef.image && mNativeTexture)
971 {
972 // If native texture is already created, and the image at this index is not available,
973 // then create a view of native texture at this index, so that modifications of the image
974 // are reflected back to native texture's respective index.
975 if (!isIndexWithinMinMaxLevels(imageIndex))
976 {
977 // Image below base level is skipped.
978 return imageDef;
979 }
980
981 mtl::MipmapNativeLevel nativeLevel = getNativeLevel(imageIndex);
982 if (nativeLevel.get() >= mNativeTexture->mipmapLevels())
983 {
984 // Image outside native texture's mip levels is skipped.
985 return imageDef;
986 }
987
988 imageDef.image = createImageViewFromNativeTexture(cubeFaceOrZero, nativeLevel);
989 imageDef.formatID = mFormat.intendedFormatId;
990 }
991
992 return imageDef;
993}
994RenderTargetMtl &TextureMtl::getRenderTarget(const gl::ImageIndex &imageIndex)
995{
996 ASSERT(imageIndex.getType() == gl::TextureType::_2D ||
997 imageIndex.getType() == gl::TextureType::Rectangle ||
998 imageIndex.getType() == gl::TextureType::_2DMultisample || imageIndex.hasLayer());
999 GLuint layer = GetImageLayerIndexFrom(imageIndex);
1000 RenderTargetMtl &rtt = mPerLayerRenderTargets[layer][imageIndex.getLevelIndex()];
1001 if (!rtt.getTexture())
1002 {
1003 // Lazy initialization of render target:
1004 mtl::TextureRef &image = getImage(imageIndex);
1005 if (image)
1006 {
1007 if (imageIndex.getType() == gl::TextureType::CubeMap)
1008 {
1009 // Cube map is special, the image is already the view of its layer
1010 rtt.set(image, mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel, 0, mFormat);
1011 }
1012 else
1013 {
1014 rtt.set(image, mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel, layer, mFormat);
1015 }
1016 }
1017 }
1018 return rtt;
1019}

1085angle::Result TextureMtl::copyImage(const gl::Context *context,
1086 const gl::ImageIndex &index,
1087 const gl::Rectangle &sourceArea,
1088 GLenum internalFormat,
1089 gl::Framebuffer *source)
1090{
1091 gl::Extents newImageSize(sourceArea.width, sourceArea.height, 1);
1092 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormatInfo =
1093 gl::GetInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE);
1094
1095 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1096 angle::FormatID angleFormatId =
1097 angle::Format::InternalFormatToID(internalFormatInfo.sizedInternalFormat);
1098 const mtl::Format &mtlFormat = contextMtl->getPixelFormat(angleFormatId);
1099
1100 FramebufferMtl *srcFramebufferMtl = mtl::GetImpl(source);
1101 RenderTargetMtl *srcReadRT = srcFramebufferMtl->getColorReadRenderTarget(context);
1102 RenderTargetMtl colorReadRT;
1103 if (srcReadRT)
1104 {
1105 // Need to duplicate RenderTargetMtl since the srcReadRT would be invalidated in
1106 // redefineImage(). This can happen if the source and this texture are the same texture.
1107 // Duplication ensures the copyImage() will be able to proceed even if the source texture
1108 // will be redefined.
1109 colorReadRT.duplicateFrom(*srcReadRT);
1110 }
1111
1112 ANGLE_TRY(redefineImage(context, index, mtlFormat, newImageSize));
1113
1114 gl::Extents fbSize = source->getReadColorAttachment()->getSize();
1115 gl::Rectangle fbRect(0, 0, fbSize.width, fbSize.height);
1116 if (context->isWebGL() && !fbRect.encloses(sourceArea))
1117 {
1118 ANGLE_TRY(initializeContents(context, index));
1119 }
1120
1121 return copySubImageImpl(context, index, gl::Offset(0, 0, 0), sourceArea, internalFormatInfo,
1122 srcFramebufferMtl, &colorReadRT);
1123}
1124
1125angle::Result TextureMtl::copySubImage(const gl::Context *context,
1126 const gl::ImageIndex &index,
1127 const gl::Offset &destOffset,
1128 const gl::Rectangle &sourceArea,
1129 gl::Framebuffer *source)
1130{
1131 const gl::InternalFormat &currentFormat = *mState.getImageDesc(index).format.info;
1132 FramebufferMtl *srcFramebufferMtl = mtl::GetImpl(source);
1133 RenderTargetMtl *colorReadRT = srcFramebufferMtl->getColorReadRenderTarget(context);
1134 return copySubImageImpl(context, index, destOffset, sourceArea, currentFormat,
1135 srcFramebufferMtl, colorReadRT);
1136}

1234angle::Result TextureMtl::setEGLImageTarget(const gl::Context *context,
1235 gl::TextureType type,
1236 egl::Image *image)
1237{
1238 releaseTexture(true);
1239
1240 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1241
1242 ImageMtl *imageMtl = mtl::GetImpl(image);
1243 if (type != imageMtl->getImageTextureType())
1244 {

1246 }

1249

1251 angle::Format::InternalFormatToID(image->getFormat().info->sizedInternalFormat);
1252 mFormat = contextMtl->getPixelFormat(angleFormatId);
1253
1254 mSlices = mNativeTexture->cubeFacesOrArrayLength();
1255

1257 mIsPow2 = gl::isPow2(size.width) && gl::isPow2(size.height) && gl::isPow2(size.depth);
1258 ANGLE_TRY(ensureSamplerStateCreated(context));

1274
1275angle::Result TextureMtl::generateMipmap(const gl::Context *context)
1276{
1277 ANGLE_TRY(ensureTextureCreated(context));
1278
1279 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1280 if (!mNativeTexture)
1281 {
1282 return angle::Result::Continue;
1283 }
1284
1285 const mtl::FormatCaps &caps = mFormat.getCaps();
1286 //
1287 bool sRGB = mFormat.actualInternalFormat().colorEncoding == GL_SRGB;
1288
1289 bool needsCPUPath = contextMtl->getDisplay()->getFeatures().intelThinMipmapWorkaround.enabled
1290 && mNativeTexture->widthAt0() < 5;
1291
1292 if (caps.writable && mState.getType() == gl::TextureType::_3D)
1293 {
1294 // http://anglebug.com/4921.
1295 // Use compute for 3D mipmap generation.
1296 ANGLE_TRY(ensureNativeLevelViewsCreated());
1297 ANGLE_TRY(contextMtl->getDisplay()->getUtils().generateMipmapCS(contextMtl, mNativeTexture,
1298 sRGB, &mNativeLevelViews));
1299 }
1300 else if (!needsCPUPath && caps.filterable && caps.colorRenderable)
1301 {
1302 mtl::BlitCommandEncoder *blitEncoder = contextMtl->getBlitCommandEncoder();
1303 blitEncoder->generateMipmapsForTexture(mNativeTexture);
1304 }
1305 else
1306 {
1307 ANGLE_TRY(generateMipmapCPU(context));
1308 }
1309
1310 return angle::Result::Continue;
1311}
1312
1313angle::Result TextureMtl::generateMipmapCPU(const gl::Context *context)
1314{
1315 ASSERT(mNativeTexture && mNativeTexture->valid());
1316
1317 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1318 const angle::Format &angleFormat = mFormat.actualAngleFormat();
1319 // This format must have mip generation function.
1320 ANGLE_MTL_TRY(contextMtl, angleFormat.mipGenerationFunction);
1321
1322 for (uint32_t slice = 0; slice < mSlices; ++slice)
1323 {
1324 mtl::MipmapNativeLevel maxMipLevel =
1325 mtl::GetNativeMipLevel(mNativeTexture->mipmapLevels() - 1, 0);
1326 const mtl::MipmapNativeLevel firstLevel = mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel;
1327
1328 uint32_t prevLevelWidth = mNativeTexture->widthAt0();
1329 uint32_t prevLevelHeight = mNativeTexture->heightAt0();
1330 uint32_t prevLevelDepth = mNativeTexture->depthAt0();
1331 size_t prevLevelRowPitch = angleFormat.pixelBytes * prevLevelWidth;
1332 size_t prevLevelDepthPitch = prevLevelRowPitch * prevLevelHeight;
1333 std::unique_ptr<uint8_t[]> prevLevelData(new (std::nothrow)
1334 uint8_t[prevLevelDepthPitch * prevLevelDepth]);
1335 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_ALLOC(contextMtl, prevLevelData);
1336 std::unique_ptr<uint8_t[]> dstLevelData;
1337
1338 // Download base level data
1339 mNativeTexture->getBytes(
1340 contextMtl, prevLevelRowPitch, prevLevelDepthPitch,
1341 MTLRegionMake3D(0, 0, 0, prevLevelWidth, prevLevelHeight, prevLevelDepth), firstLevel,
1342 slice, prevLevelData.get());
1343
1344 for (mtl::MipmapNativeLevel mip = firstLevel + 1; mip <= maxMipLevel; ++mip)
1345 {
1346 uint32_t dstWidth = mNativeTexture->width(mip);
1347 uint32_t dstHeight = mNativeTexture->height(mip);
1348 uint32_t dstDepth = mNativeTexture->depth(mip);
1349
1350 size_t dstRowPitch = angleFormat.pixelBytes * dstWidth;
1351 size_t dstDepthPitch = dstRowPitch * dstHeight;
1352 size_t dstDataSize = dstDepthPitch * dstDepth;
1353 if (!dstLevelData)
1354 {
1355 // Allocate once and reuse the buffer
1356 dstLevelData.reset(new (std::nothrow) uint8_t[dstDataSize]);
1357 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_ALLOC(contextMtl, dstLevelData);
1358 }
1359
1360 // Generate mip level
1361 angleFormat.mipGenerationFunction(
1362 prevLevelWidth, prevLevelHeight, 1, prevLevelData.get(), prevLevelRowPitch,
1363 prevLevelDepthPitch, dstLevelData.get(), dstRowPitch, dstDepthPitch);
1364
1365 // Upload to texture
1366 ANGLE_TRY(UploadTextureContents(
1367 context, angleFormat, MTLRegionMake3D(0, 0, 0, dstWidth, dstHeight, dstDepth), mip,
1368 slice, dstLevelData.get(), dstRowPitch, dstDepthPitch, mNativeTexture));
1369
1370 prevLevelWidth = dstWidth;
1371 prevLevelHeight = dstHeight;
1372 prevLevelDepth = dstDepth;
1373 prevLevelRowPitch = dstRowPitch;
1374 prevLevelDepthPitch = dstDepthPitch;
1375 std::swap(prevLevelData, dstLevelData);
1376 } // for mip level
1377
1378 } // For layers
1379
1380 return angle::Result::Continue;
1381}

1383angle::Result TextureMtl::setBaseLevel(const gl::Context *context, GLuint baseLevel)
1384{
1385 return onBaseMaxLevelsChanged(context);
1386}

1427
1428angle::Result TextureMtl::syncState(const gl::Context *context,
1429 const gl::Texture::DirtyBits &dirtyBits,
1430 gl::Command source)
1431{
1432 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1433 for (size_t dirtyBit : dirtyBits)
1434 {
1435 switch (dirtyBit)
1436 {
1437 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_COMPARE_MODE:
1438 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_COMPARE_FUNC:
1439 // Tell context to rebind textures so that ProgramMtl has a chance to verify
1440 // depth texture compare mode.
1441 contextMtl->invalidateCurrentTextures();
1442 // fall through
1443 OS_FALLTHROUGH;
1444 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_MIN_FILTER:
1445 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_MAG_FILTER:
1446 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_WRAP_S:
1447 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_WRAP_T:
1448 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_WRAP_R:
1449 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_MAX_ANISOTROPY:
1450 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_MIN_LOD:
1451 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_MAX_LOD:
1452 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_SRGB_DECODE:
1453 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_BORDER_COLOR:
1454 // Recreate sampler state
1455 mMetalSamplerState = nil;
1456 break;
1457 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_MAX_LEVEL:
1458 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_BASE_LEVEL:
1459 ANGLE_TRY(onBaseMaxLevelsChanged(context));
1460 break;
1461 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_SWIZZLE_RED:
1462 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_SWIZZLE_GREEN:
1463 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_SWIZZLE_BLUE:
1464 case gl::Texture::DIRTY_BIT_SWIZZLE_ALPHA:
1465 {
1466 // Recreate swizzle view.
1467 mNativeSwizzleSamplingView = nullptr;
1468 }
1469 break;
1470 default:
1471 break;
1472 }
1473 }
1474
1475 ANGLE_TRY(ensureTextureCreated(context));
1476 ANGLE_TRY(ensureSamplerStateCreated(context));
1477
1478 return angle::Result::Continue;
1479}
1480
1481angle::Result TextureMtl::bindToShader(const gl::Context *context,
1482 mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1483 gl::ShaderType shaderType,
1484 gl::Sampler *sampler,
1485 int textureSlotIndex,
1486 int samplerSlotIndex)
1487{
1488 ASSERT(mNativeTexture);
1489
1490 float minLodClamp;
1491 float maxLodClamp;
1492 id<MTLSamplerState> samplerState;
1493
1494 if (!mNativeSwizzleSamplingView)
1495 {
1496#if ANGLE_MTL_SWIZZLE_AVAILABLE
1497 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1498
1499 if ((mState.getSwizzleState().swizzleRequired() || mFormat.actualAngleFormat().depthBits ||
1500 mFormat.swizzled) &&
1501 contextMtl->getDisplay()->getFeatures().hasTextureSwizzle.enabled)
1502 {
1503 const gl::InternalFormat &glInternalFormat = *mState.getBaseLevelDesc().format.info;
1504
1505 MTLTextureSwizzleChannels swizzle = MTLTextureSwizzleChannelsMake(
1506 mtl::GetTextureSwizzle(OverrideSwizzleValue(
1507 context, mState.getSwizzleState().swizzleRed, mFormat, glInternalFormat)),
1508 mtl::GetTextureSwizzle(OverrideSwizzleValue(
1509 context, mState.getSwizzleState().swizzleGreen, mFormat, glInternalFormat)),
1510 mtl::GetTextureSwizzle(OverrideSwizzleValue(
1511 context, mState.getSwizzleState().swizzleBlue, mFormat, glInternalFormat)),
1512 mtl::GetTextureSwizzle(OverrideSwizzleValue(
1513 context, mState.getSwizzleState().swizzleAlpha, mFormat, glInternalFormat)));
1514
1515 mNativeSwizzleSamplingView = mNativeTexture->createSwizzleView(swizzle);
1516 }
1517 else
1518#endif // ANGLE_MTL_SWIZZLE_AVAILABLE
1519 {
1520 mNativeSwizzleSamplingView = mNativeTexture;
1521 }
1522 }
1523
1524 if (!sampler)
1525 {
1526 samplerState = mMetalSamplerState;
1527 minLodClamp = mState.getSamplerState().getMinLod();
1528 maxLodClamp = mState.getSamplerState().getMaxLod();
1529 }
1530 else
1531 {
1532 SamplerMtl *samplerMtl = mtl::GetImpl(sampler);
1533 samplerState = samplerMtl->getSampler(mtl::GetImpl(context));
1534 minLodClamp = sampler->getSamplerState().getMinLod();
1535 maxLodClamp = sampler->getSamplerState().getMaxLod();
1536 }
1537
1538 minLodClamp = std::max(minLodClamp, 0.f);
1539
1540 cmdEncoder->setTexture(shaderType, mNativeSwizzleSamplingView, textureSlotIndex);
1541 cmdEncoder->setSamplerState(shaderType, samplerState, minLodClamp, maxLodClamp,
1542 samplerSlotIndex);
1543
1544 return angle::Result::Continue;
1545}
1546
1547angle::Result TextureMtl::redefineImage(const gl::Context *context,
1548 const gl::ImageIndex &index,
1549 const mtl::Format &mtlFormat,
1550 const gl::Extents &size)
1551{
1552 bool imageWithinLevelRange = false;
1553 if (isIndexWithinMinMaxLevels(index) && mNativeTexture && mNativeTexture->valid())
1554 {
1555 imageWithinLevelRange = true;
1556 mtl::MipmapNativeLevel nativeLevel = getNativeLevel(index);
1557 // Calculate the expected size for the index we are defining. If the size is different
1558 // from the given size, or the format is different, we are redefining the image so we
1559 // must release it.
1560 bool typeChanged = mNativeTexture->textureType() != mtl::GetTextureType(index.getType());
1561 if (mFormat != mtlFormat || size != mNativeTexture->size(nativeLevel) || typeChanged)
1562 {
1563 // Keep other images data if texture type hasn't been changed.
1564 releaseTexture(typeChanged);
1565 }
1566 }
1567
1568 // Early-out on empty textures, don't create a zero-sized storage.
1569 if (size.empty())
1570 {
1571 return angle::Result::Continue;
1572 }
1573
1574 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1575 // Cache last defined image format:
1576 mFormat = mtlFormat;
1577 ImageDefinitionMtl &imageDef = getImageDefinition(index);
1578
1579 // If native texture still exists, it means the size hasn't been changed, no need to create new
1580 // image
1581 if (mNativeTexture && imageDef.image && imageWithinLevelRange)
1582 {
1583 ASSERT(imageDef.image->textureType() ==
1584 mtl::GetTextureType(GetTextureImageType(index.getType())) &&
1585 imageDef.formatID == mFormat.intendedFormatId && imageDef.image->sizeAt0() == size);
1586 }
1587 else
1588 {
1589 imageDef.formatID = mtlFormat.intendedFormatId;
1590 // Create image to hold texture's data at this level & slice:
1591 switch (index.getType())
1592 {
1593 case gl::TextureType::_2D:
1594 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
1595 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::Texture::Make2DTexture(
1596 contextMtl, mtlFormat, size.width, size.height, 1,
1597 /** renderTargetOnly */ false,
1598 /** allowFormatView */ mFormat.hasDepthAndStencilBits(), &imageDef.image));
1599 break;
1600 case gl::TextureType::_3D:
1601 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::Texture::Make3DTexture(
1602 contextMtl, mtlFormat, size.width, size.height, size.depth, 1,
1603 /** renderTargetOnly */ false,
1604 /** allowFormatView */ mFormat.hasDepthAndStencilBits(), &imageDef.image));
1605 break;
1606 case gl::TextureType::_2DArray:
1607 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::Texture::Make2DArrayTexture(
1608 contextMtl, mtlFormat, size.width, size.height, 1, size.depth,
1609 /** renderTargetOnly */ false,
1610 /** allowFormatView */ mFormat.hasDepthAndStencilBits(), &imageDef.image));
1611 break;
1612 default:
1613 UNREACHABLE();
1614 }
1615 }
1616
1617 // Make sure emulated channels are properly initialized
1618 ANGLE_TRY(checkForEmulatedChannels(context, mtlFormat, imageDef.image));
1619
1620 // Tell context to rebind textures
1621 contextMtl->invalidateCurrentTextures();
1622
1623 return angle::Result::Continue;
1624}
1625
1626// If mipmaps = 0, this function will create full mipmaps texture.
1627angle::Result TextureMtl::setStorageImpl(const gl::Context *context,
1628 gl::TextureType type,
1629 size_t mipmaps,
1630 const mtl::Format &mtlFormat,
1631 const gl::Extents &size)
1632{
1633 // Don't need to hold old images data.
1634 releaseTexture(true);
1635
1636 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1637
1638 // Tell context to rebind textures
1639 contextMtl->invalidateCurrentTextures();
1640
1641 mFormat = mtlFormat;
1642
1643 // Texture will be created later in ensureTextureCreated()
1644
1645 return angle::Result::Continue;
1646}
1647
1648angle::Result TextureMtl::setImageImpl(const gl::Context *context,
1649 const gl::ImageIndex &index,
1650 const gl::InternalFormat &dstFormatInfo,
1651 const gl::Extents &size,
1652 GLenum srcFormat,
1653 GLenum srcType,
1654 const gl::PixelUnpackState &unpack,
1655 gl::Buffer *unpackBuffer,
1656 const uint8_t *pixels)
1657{
1658 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1659 angle::FormatID angleFormatId =
1660 angle::Format::InternalFormatToID(dstFormatInfo.sizedInternalFormat);
1661 const mtl::Format &mtlFormat = contextMtl->getPixelFormat(angleFormatId);
1662
1663 ANGLE_TRY(redefineImage(context, index, mtlFormat, size));
1664
1665 // Early-out on empty textures, don't create a zero-sized storage.
1666 if (size.empty())
1667 {
1668 return angle::Result::Continue;
1669 }
1670
1671 // Format of the supplied pixels.
1672 const gl::InternalFormat *srcFormatInfo;
1673 if (srcFormat != dstFormatInfo.format || srcType != dstFormatInfo.type)
1674 {
1675 srcFormatInfo = &gl::GetInternalFormatInfo(srcFormat, srcType);
1676 }
1677 else
1678 {
1679 srcFormatInfo = &dstFormatInfo;
1680 }
1681 return setSubImageImpl(context, index, gl::Box(0, 0, 0, size.width, size.height, size.depth),
1682 *srcFormatInfo, srcType, unpack, unpackBuffer, pixels);
1683}
1684
1685angle::Result TextureMtl::setSubImageImpl(const gl::Context *context,
1686 const gl::ImageIndex &index,
1687 const gl::Box &area,
1688 const gl::InternalFormat &formatInfo,
1689 GLenum type,
1690 const gl::PixelUnpackState &unpack,
1691 gl::Buffer *unpackBuffer,
1692 const uint8_t *oriPixels)
1693{
1694 if (!oriPixels && !unpackBuffer)
1695 {
1696 return angle::Result::Continue;
1697 }
1698
1699 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1700
1701 ANGLE_TRY(ensureImageCreated(context, index));
1702 mtl::TextureRef &image = getImage(index);
1703
1704 GLuint sourceRowPitch = 0;
1705 GLuint sourceDepthPitch = 0;
1706 GLuint sourceSkipBytes = 0;
1707 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_MATH(contextMtl, formatInfo.computeRowPitch(type, area.width, unpack.alignment,
1708 unpack.rowLength, &sourceRowPitch));
1709 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_MATH(
1710 contextMtl, formatInfo.computeDepthPitch(area.height, unpack.imageHeight, sourceRowPitch,
1711 &sourceDepthPitch));
1712 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_MATH(contextMtl,
1713 formatInfo.computeSkipBytes(type, sourceRowPitch, sourceDepthPitch, unpack,
1714 index.usesTex3D(), &sourceSkipBytes));
1715
1716 // Check if partial image update is supported for this format
1717 if (!formatInfo.supportSubImage())
1718 {
1719 // area must be the whole mip level
1720 sourceRowPitch = 0;
1721 gl::Extents size = image->sizeAt0();
1722 if (area.x != 0 || area.y != 0 || area.width != size.width || area.height != size.height)
1723 {
1724 ANGLE_MTL_CHECK(contextMtl, false, GL_INVALID_OPERATION);
1725 }
1726 }
1727
1728 // Get corresponding source data's ANGLE format
1729 angle::FormatID srcAngleFormatId;
1730 if (formatInfo.sizedInternalFormat == GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT24)
1731 {
1732 // GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT24 is special case, its supplied data is 32 bit depth.
1733 srcAngleFormatId = angle::FormatID::D32_UNORM;
1734 }
1735 else
1736 {
1737 srcAngleFormatId = angle::Format::InternalFormatToID(formatInfo.sizedInternalFormat);
1738 }
1739 const angle::Format &srcAngleFormat = angle::Format::Get(srcAngleFormatId);
1740
1741 const uint8_t *usablePixels = oriPixels + sourceSkipBytes;
1742
1743 // Upload to texture
1744 if (index.getType() == gl::TextureType::_2DArray)
1745 {
1746 // OpenGL unifies texture array and texture 3d's box area by using z & depth as array start
1747 // index & length for texture array. However, Metal treats them differently. We need to
1748 // handle them in separate code.
1749 MTLRegion mtlRegion = MTLRegionMake3D(area.x, area.y, 0, area.width, area.height, 1);
1750
1751 for (int slice = 0; slice < area.depth; ++slice)
1752 {
1753 int sliceIndex = slice + area.z;
1754 const uint8_t *srcPixels = usablePixels + slice * sourceDepthPitch;
1755 ANGLE_TRY(setPerSliceSubImage(context, sliceIndex, mtlRegion, formatInfo, type,
1756 srcAngleFormat, sourceRowPitch, sourceDepthPitch,
1757 unpackBuffer, srcPixels, image));
1758 }
1759 }
1760 else
1761 {
1762 MTLRegion mtlRegion =
1763 MTLRegionMake3D(area.x, area.y, area.z, area.width, area.height, area.depth);
1764
1765 ANGLE_TRY(setPerSliceSubImage(context, 0, mtlRegion, formatInfo, type, srcAngleFormat,
1766 sourceRowPitch, sourceDepthPitch, unpackBuffer, usablePixels,
1767 image));
1768 }
1769
1770 return angle::Result::Continue;
1771}
1772
1773angle::Result TextureMtl::setPerSliceSubImage(const gl::Context *context,
1774 int slice,
1775 const MTLRegion &mtlArea,
1776 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat,
1777 GLenum type,
1778 const angle::Format &pixelsAngleFormat,
1779 size_t pixelsRowPitch,
1780 size_t pixelsDepthPitch,
1781 gl::Buffer *unpackBuffer,
1782 const uint8_t *pixels,
1783 const mtl::TextureRef &image)
1784{
1785 // If source pixels are luminance or RGB8, we need to convert them to RGBA
1786
1787 if (mFormat.needConversion(pixelsAngleFormat.id))
1788 {
1789 return convertAndSetPerSliceSubImage(context, slice, mtlArea, internalFormat, type,
1790 pixelsAngleFormat, pixelsRowPitch, pixelsDepthPitch,
1791 unpackBuffer, pixels, image);
1792 }
1793
1794 // No conversion needed.
1795 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1796
1797 if (unpackBuffer)
1798 {
1799 uintptr_t offset = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(pixels);
1800 GLuint minRowPitch;
1801 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_MATH(contextMtl, internalFormat.computeRowPitch(
1802 type, static_cast<GLint>(mtlArea.size.width),
1803 /** aligment */ 1, /** rowLength */ 0, &minRowPitch));
1804 if (offset % mFormat.actualAngleFormat().pixelBytes || pixelsRowPitch < minRowPitch)
1805 {
1806 // offset is not divisible by pixelByte or the source row pitch is smaller than minimum
1807 // row pitch, use convertAndSetPerSliceSubImage() function.
1808 return convertAndSetPerSliceSubImage(context, slice, mtlArea, internalFormat, type,
1809 pixelsAngleFormat, pixelsRowPitch,
1810 pixelsDepthPitch, unpackBuffer, pixels, image);
1811 }
1812
1813 BufferMtl *unpackBufferMtl = mtl::GetImpl(unpackBuffer);
1814
1815 if (mFormat.hasDepthAndStencilBits())
1816 {
1817 // NOTE(hqle): packed depth & stencil texture cannot copy from buffer directly, needs
1818 // to split its depth & stencil data and copy separately.
1819 const uint8_t *clientData = unpackBufferMtl->getClientShadowCopyData(contextMtl);
1820 clientData += offset;
1821 ANGLE_TRY(UploadTextureContents(context, mFormat.actualAngleFormat(), mtlArea,
1822 mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel, slice, clientData,
1823 pixelsRowPitch, pixelsDepthPitch, image));
1824 }
1825 else
1826 {
1827 // Use blit encoder to copy
1828 mtl::BlitCommandEncoder *blitEncoder = contextMtl->getBlitCommandEncoder();
1829 blitEncoder->copyBufferToTexture(
1830 unpackBufferMtl->getCurrentBuffer(), offset, pixelsRowPitch, pixelsDepthPitch,
1831 mtlArea.size, image, slice, mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel, mtlArea.origin,
1832 mFormat.isPVRTC() ? mtl::kBlitOptionRowLinearPVRTC : MTLBlitOptionNone);
1833 }
1834 }
1835 else
1836 {
1837 // Upload texture data directly
1838 ANGLE_TRY(UploadTextureContents(context, mFormat.actualAngleFormat(), mtlArea,
1839 mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel, slice, pixels, pixelsRowPitch,
1840 pixelsDepthPitch, image));
1841 }
1842 return angle::Result::Continue;
1843}
1844
1845angle::Result TextureMtl::convertAndSetPerSliceSubImage(const gl::Context *context,
1846 int slice,
1847 const MTLRegion &mtlArea,
1848 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat,
1849 GLenum type,
1850 const angle::Format &pixelsAngleFormat,
1851 size_t pixelsRowPitch,
1852 size_t pixelsDepthPitch,
1853 gl::Buffer *unpackBuffer,
1854 const uint8_t *pixels,
1855 const mtl::TextureRef &image)
1856{
1857 ASSERT(image && image->valid());
1858
1859 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1860
1861 if (unpackBuffer)
1862 {
1863 ANGLE_MTL_CHECK(contextMtl,
1864 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(pixels) <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max(),
1865 GL_INVALID_OPERATION);
1866
1867 uint32_t offset = static_cast<uint32_t>(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(pixels));
1868
1869 BufferMtl *unpackBufferMtl = mtl::GetImpl(unpackBuffer);
1870 if (!mFormat.getCaps().writable || mFormat.hasDepthOrStencilBits() ||
1871 mFormat.intendedAngleFormat().isBlock)
1872 {
1873 // Unsupported format, use CPU path.
1874 const uint8_t *clientData = unpackBufferMtl->getClientShadowCopyData(contextMtl);
1875 clientData += offset;
1876 ANGLE_TRY(convertAndSetPerSliceSubImage(context, slice, mtlArea, internalFormat, type,
1877 pixelsAngleFormat, pixelsRowPitch,
1878 pixelsDepthPitch, nullptr, clientData, image));
1879 }
1880 else
1881 {
1882 // Use compute shader
1883 mtl::CopyPixelsFromBufferParams params;
1884 params.buffer = unpackBufferMtl->getCurrentBuffer();
1885 params.bufferStartOffset = offset;
1886 params.bufferRowPitch = static_cast<uint32_t>(pixelsRowPitch);
1887 params.bufferDepthPitch = static_cast<uint32_t>(pixelsDepthPitch);
1888 params.texture = image;
1889 params.textureArea = mtl::MTLRegionToGLBox(mtlArea);
1890
1891 // If texture is not array, slice must be zero, if texture is array, mtlArea.origin.z
1892 // must be zero.
1893 // This is because this function uses Metal convention: where slice is only used for
1894 // array textures, and z layer of mtlArea.origin is only used for 3D textures.
1895 ASSERT(slice == 0 || params.textureArea.z == 0);
1896
1897 // For mtl::RenderUtils we convert to OpenGL convention: z layer is used as either array
1898 // texture's slice or 3D texture's layer index.
1899 params.textureArea.z += slice;
1900
1901 ANGLE_TRY(contextMtl->getDisplay()->getUtils().unpackPixelsFromBufferToTexture(
1902 contextMtl, pixelsAngleFormat, params));
1903 }
1904 } // if (unpackBuffer)
1905 else
1906 {
1907 LoadImageFunctionInfo loadFunctionInfo = mFormat.textureLoadFunctions
1908 ? mFormat.textureLoadFunctions(type)
1909 : LoadImageFunctionInfo();
1910 const angle::Format &dstFormat = angle::Format::Get(mFormat.actualFormatId);
1911 const size_t dstRowPitch = dstFormat.pixelBytes * mtlArea.size.width;
1912
1913 // Check if original image data is compressed:
1914 if (mFormat.intendedAngleFormat().isBlock)
1915 {
1916 if(mFormat.intendedFormatId != mFormat.actualFormatId)
1917 {
1918 ASSERT(loadFunctionInfo.loadFunction);
1919
1920 // Need to create a buffer to hold entire decompressed image.
1921 const size_t dstDepthPitch = dstRowPitch * mtlArea.size.height;
1922 angle::MemoryBuffer decompressBuf;
1923 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_ALLOC(contextMtl,
1924 decompressBuf.resize(dstDepthPitch * mtlArea.size.depth));
1925
1926 // Decompress
1927 loadFunctionInfo.loadFunction(
1928 mtlArea.size.width, mtlArea.size.height, mtlArea.size.depth, pixels, pixelsRowPitch,
1929 pixelsDepthPitch, decompressBuf.data(), dstRowPitch, dstDepthPitch);
1930
1931 // Upload to texture
1932 ANGLE_TRY(UploadTextureContents(context, dstFormat, mtlArea, mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel,
1933 slice, decompressBuf.data(), dstRowPitch, dstDepthPitch,
1934 image));
1935 }
1936 else
1937 {
1938 //Assert that we're filling the level in it's entierety.
1939 ASSERT(mtlArea.size.width == image->sizeAt0().width);
1940 ASSERT(mtlArea.size.height == image->sizeAt0().height);
1941 const size_t dstDepthPitch = dstRowPitch * mtlArea.size.height;
1942 ANGLE_TRY(UploadTextureContents(context, dstFormat, mtlArea, mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel,
1943 slice, pixels, dstRowPitch, dstDepthPitch,
1944 image));
1945 }
1946 } // if (mFormat.intendedAngleFormat().isBlock)
1947 else
1948 {
1949 // Create scratch row buffer
1950 angle::MemoryBuffer conversionRow;
1951 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_ALLOC(contextMtl, conversionRow.resize(dstRowPitch));
1952
1953 // Convert row by row:
1954 MTLRegion mtlRow = mtlArea;
1955 mtlRow.size.height = mtlRow.size.depth = 1;
1956 for (NSUInteger d = 0; d < mtlArea.size.depth; ++d)
1957 {
1958 mtlRow.origin.z = mtlArea.origin.z + d;
1959 for (NSUInteger r = 0; r < mtlArea.size.height; ++r)
1960 {
1961 const uint8_t *psrc = pixels + d * pixelsDepthPitch + r * pixelsRowPitch;
1962 mtlRow.origin.y = mtlArea.origin.y + r;
1963
1964 // Convert pixels
1965 if (loadFunctionInfo.loadFunction)
1966 {
1967 loadFunctionInfo.loadFunction(mtlRow.size.width, 1, 1, psrc, pixelsRowPitch,
1968 0, conversionRow.data(), dstRowPitch, 0);
1969 }
1970 else if (mFormat.hasDepthOrStencilBits())
1971 {
1972 ConvertDepthStencilData(mtlRow.size, pixelsAngleFormat, pixelsRowPitch, 0,
1973 psrc, dstFormat, nullptr, dstRowPitch, 0,
1974 conversionRow.data());
1975 }
1976 else
1977 {
1978 CopyImageCHROMIUM(psrc, pixelsRowPitch, pixelsAngleFormat.pixelBytes, 0,
1979 pixelsAngleFormat.pixelReadFunction, conversionRow.data(),
1980 dstRowPitch, dstFormat.pixelBytes, 0,
1981 dstFormat.pixelWriteFunction, internalFormat.format,
1982 dstFormat.componentType, mtlRow.size.width, 1, 1, false,
1983 false, false);
1984 }
1985
1986 // Upload to texture
1987 ANGLE_TRY(UploadTextureContents(context, dstFormat, mtlRow,
1988 mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel, slice,
1989 conversionRow.data(), dstRowPitch, 0, image));
1990 }
1991 }
1992 } // if (mFormat.intendedAngleFormat().isBlock)
1993 } // if (unpackBuffer)
1994
1995 return angle::Result::Continue;
1996}

1998angle::Result TextureMtl::checkForEmulatedChannels(const gl::Context *context,
1999 const mtl::Format &mtlFormat,
2000 const mtl::TextureRef &texture)
2001{
2002 bool emulatedChannels = mtl::IsFormatEmulated(mtlFormat);
2003
2004 // For emulated channels that GL texture intends to not have,
2005 // we need to initialize their content.
2006 if (emulatedChannels)
2007 {
2008 uint32_t mipmaps = texture->mipmapLevels();
2009
2010 uint32_t layers = texture->cubeFacesOrArrayLength();
2011 for (uint32_t layer = 0; layer < layers; ++layer)
2012 {
2013 for (uint32_t mip = 0; mip < mipmaps; ++mip)
2014 {
2015 auto index = mtl::ImageNativeIndex::FromBaseZeroGLIndex(
2016 GetCubeOrArraySliceMipIndex(texture, layer, mip));
2017
2018 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::InitializeTextureContents(context, texture, mtlFormat, index));
2019 }
2020 }
2021 }
2022 return angle::Result::Continue;
2023}
2024
2025angle::Result TextureMtl::initializeContents(const gl::Context *context,
2026 const gl::ImageIndex &index)
2027{
2028 if (index.isLayered())
2029 {
2030 // InitializeTextureContents is only able to initialize one layer at a time.
2031 const gl::ImageDesc &desc = mState.getImageDesc(index);
2032 uint32_t layerCount;
2033 if (index.isEntireLevelCubeMap())
2034 {
2035 layerCount = 6;
2036 }
2037 else
2038 {
2039 layerCount = desc.size.depth;
2040 }
2041
2042 gl::ImageIndexIterator ite = index.getLayerIterator(layerCount);
2043 while (ite.hasNext())
2044 {
2045 gl::ImageIndex layerIndex = ite.next();
2046 ANGLE_TRY(initializeContents(context, layerIndex));
2047 }
2048 return angle::Result::Continue;
2049 }
2050 else if (index.getLayerCount() > 1)
2051 {
2052 for (int layer = 0; layer < index.getLayerCount(); ++layer)
2053 {
2054 int layerIdx = layer + index.getLayerIndex();
2055 gl::ImageIndex layerIndex =
2056 gl::ImageIndex::MakeFromType(index.getType(), index.getLevelIndex(), layerIdx);
2057 ANGLE_TRY(initializeContents(context, layerIndex));
2058 }
2059 return angle::Result::Continue;
2060 }
2061
2062 ASSERT(index.getLayerCount() == 1 && !index.isLayered());
2063 ANGLE_TRY(ensureImageCreated(context, index));
2064 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
2065 ImageDefinitionMtl &imageDef = getImageDefinition(index);
2066 const mtl::TextureRef &image = imageDef.image;
2067 const mtl::Format &format = contextMtl->getPixelFormat(imageDef.formatID);
2068 // For Texture's image definition, we always use zero mip level.
2069 if (format.metalFormat == MTLPixelFormatInvalid)
2070 {
2071 return angle::Result::Stop;
2072 }
2073 return mtl::InitializeTextureContents(
2074 context, image, format,
2075 mtl::ImageNativeIndex::FromBaseZeroGLIndex(
2076 GetLayerMipIndex(image, GetImageLayerIndexFrom(index), /** level */ 0)));
2077}

2079angle::Result TextureMtl::copySubImageImpl(const gl::Context *context,
2080 const gl::ImageIndex &index,
2081 const gl::Offset &destOffset,
2082 const gl::Rectangle &sourceArea,
2083 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat,
2084 const FramebufferMtl *source,
2085 const RenderTargetMtl *colorReadRT)
2086{
2087 if (!colorReadRT || !colorReadRT->getTexture())
2088 {
2089 // Is this an error?
2090 return angle::Result::Continue;
2091 }
2092
2093 gl::Extents fbSize = colorReadRT->getTexture()->size(colorReadRT->getLevelIndex());
2094 gl::Rectangle clippedSourceArea;
2095 if (!ClipRectangle(sourceArea, gl::Rectangle(0, 0, fbSize.width, fbSize.height),
2096 &clippedSourceArea))
2097 {
2098 return angle::Result::Continue;
2099 }
2100
2101 // If negative offsets are given, clippedSourceArea ensures we don't read from those offsets.
2102 // However, that changes the sourceOffset->destOffset mapping. Here, destOffset is shifted by
2103 // the same amount as clipped to correct the error.
2104 const gl::Offset modifiedDestOffset(destOffset.x + clippedSourceArea.x - sourceArea.x,
2105 destOffset.y + clippedSourceArea.y - sourceArea.y, 0);
2106
2107 ANGLE_TRY(ensureImageCreated(context, index));
2108
2109 if (!mFormat.getCaps().isRenderable())
2110 {
2111 return copySubImageCPU(context, index, modifiedDestOffset, clippedSourceArea,
2112 internalFormat, source, colorReadRT);
2113 }
2114
2115 // NOTE(hqle): Use compute shader.
2116 return copySubImageWithDraw(context, index, modifiedDestOffset, clippedSourceArea,
2117 internalFormat, source, colorReadRT);
2118}

2120angle::Result TextureMtl::copySubImageWithDraw(const gl::Context *context,
2121 const gl::ImageIndex &index,
2122 const gl::Offset &modifiedDestOffset,
2123 const gl::Rectangle &clippedSourceArea,
2124 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat,
2125 const FramebufferMtl *source,
2126 const RenderTargetMtl *colorReadRT)
2127{
2128 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
2129 DisplayMtl *displayMtl = contextMtl->getDisplay();
2130
2131 const RenderTargetMtl &imageRtt = getRenderTarget(index);
2132
2133 mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder = contextMtl->getRenderTargetCommandEncoder(imageRtt);
2134 mtl::ColorBlitParams blitParams;
2135
2136 blitParams.dstTextureSize = imageRtt.getTexture()->size(imageRtt.getLevelIndex());
2137 blitParams.dstRect = gl::Rectangle(modifiedDestOffset.x, modifiedDestOffset.y,
2138 clippedSourceArea.width, clippedSourceArea.height);
2139 blitParams.dstScissorRect = blitParams.dstRect;
2140
2141 blitParams.enabledBuffers.set(0);
2142
2143 blitParams.src = colorReadRT->getTexture();
2144 blitParams.srcLevel = colorReadRT->getLevelIndex();
2145 blitParams.srcLayer = colorReadRT->getLayerIndex();
2146 blitParams.srcRect = clippedSourceArea;
2147 blitParams.srcYFlipped = source->flipY();
2148 blitParams.dstLuminance = internalFormat.isLUMA();

2150 return displayMtl->getUtils().blitColorWithDraw(
2151 context, cmdEncoder, colorReadRT->getFormat()->actualAngleFormat(), blitParams);

2154angle::Result TextureMtl::copySubImageCPU(const gl::Context *context,
2155 const gl::ImageIndex &index,
2156 const gl::Offset &modifiedDestOffset,
2157 const gl::Rectangle &clippedSourceArea,
2158 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat,
2159 const FramebufferMtl *source,
2160 const RenderTargetMtl *colorReadRT)
2161{
2162 mtl::TextureRef &image = getImage(index);
2163 ASSERT(image && image->valid());
2164
2165 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
2166
2167 const angle::Format &dstFormat = angle::Format::Get(mFormat.actualFormatId);
2168 const int dstRowPitch = dstFormat.pixelBytes * clippedSourceArea.width;
2169 angle::MemoryBuffer conversionRow;
2170 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_ALLOC(contextMtl, conversionRow.resize(dstRowPitch));
2171
2172 gl::Rectangle srcRowArea = gl::Rectangle(clippedSourceArea.x, 0, clippedSourceArea.width, 1);
2173 MTLRegion mtlDstRowArea = MTLRegionMake2D(modifiedDestOffset.x, 0, clippedSourceArea.width, 1);
2174 uint32_t dstSlice = 0;
2175 switch (index.getType())
2176 {
2177 case gl::TextureType::_2D:
2178 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
2179 dstSlice = 0;
2180 break;
2181 case gl::TextureType::_2DArray:
2182 ASSERT(index.hasLayer());
2183 dstSlice = index.getLayerIndex();
2184 break;
2185 case gl::TextureType::_3D:
2186 ASSERT(index.hasLayer());
2187 dstSlice = 0;
2188 mtlDstRowArea.origin.z = index.getLayerIndex();
2189 break;
2190 default:
2191 UNREACHABLE();
2192 }
2193
2194 // Copy row by row:
2195 for (int r = 0; r < clippedSourceArea.height; ++r)
2196 {
2197 mtlDstRowArea.origin.y = modifiedDestOffset.y + r;
2198 srcRowArea.y = clippedSourceArea.y + r;
2199
2200 PackPixelsParams packParams(srcRowArea, dstFormat, dstRowPitch, false, nullptr, 0);
2201
2202 // Read pixels from framebuffer to memory:
2203 gl::Rectangle flippedSrcRowArea = source->getCorrectFlippedReadArea(context, srcRowArea);
2204 ANGLE_TRY(source->readPixelsImpl(context, flippedSrcRowArea, packParams, colorReadRT,
2205 conversionRow.data()));
2206
2207 // Upload to texture
2208 ANGLE_TRY(UploadTextureContents(context, dstFormat, mtlDstRowArea, mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel,
2209 dstSlice, conversionRow.data(), dstRowPitch, 0, image));
2210 }
2211
2212 return angle::Result::Continue;
2213}

2250 return copySubTextureWithDraw(

2303angle::Result TextureMtl::copySubTextureCPU(const gl::Context *context,
2304 const gl::ImageIndex &index,
2305 const gl::Offset &destOffset,
2306 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat,
2307 const mtl::MipmapNativeLevel &sourceNativeLevel,
2308 const gl::Box &sourceBox,
2309 const angle::Format &sourceAngleFormat,
2310 bool unpackFlipY,
2311 bool unpackPremultiplyAlpha,
2312 bool unpackUnmultiplyAlpha,
2313 const mtl::TextureRef &sourceTexture)
2314{
2315 mtl::TextureRef &image = getImage(index);
2316 ASSERT(image && image->valid());
2317
2318 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
2319
2320 const angle::Format &dstAngleFormat = mFormat.actualAngleFormat();
2321 const int srcRowPitch = sourceAngleFormat.pixelBytes * sourceBox.width;
2322 const int srcImageSize = srcRowPitch * sourceBox.height;
2323 const int convRowPitch = dstAngleFormat.pixelBytes * sourceBox.width;
2324 const int convImageSize = convRowPitch * sourceBox.height;
2325 angle::MemoryBuffer conversionSrc, conversionDst;
2326 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_ALLOC(contextMtl, conversionSrc.resize(srcImageSize));
2327 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_ALLOC(contextMtl, conversionDst.resize(convImageSize));
2328
2329 MTLRegion mtlSrcArea =
2330 MTLRegionMake2D(sourceBox.x, sourceBox.y, sourceBox.width, sourceBox.height);
2331 MTLRegion mtlDstArea =
2332 MTLRegionMake2D(destOffset.x, destOffset.y, sourceBox.width, sourceBox.height);
2333
2334 // Read pixels from source to memory:
2335 sourceTexture->getBytes(contextMtl, srcRowPitch, 0, mtlSrcArea, sourceNativeLevel, 0,
2336 conversionSrc.data());
2337
2338 // Convert to destination format
2339 CopyImageCHROMIUM(conversionSrc.data(), srcRowPitch, sourceAngleFormat.pixelBytes, 0,
2340 sourceAngleFormat.pixelReadFunction, conversionDst.data(), convRowPitch,
2341 dstAngleFormat.pixelBytes, 0, dstAngleFormat.pixelWriteFunction,
2342 internalFormat.format, internalFormat.componentType, sourceBox.width,
2343 sourceBox.height, 1, unpackFlipY, unpackPremultiplyAlpha,
2344 unpackUnmultiplyAlpha);
2345
2346 // Upload to texture
2347 ANGLE_TRY(UploadTextureContents(context, dstAngleFormat, mtlDstArea, mtl::kZeroNativeMipLevel,
2348 0, conversionDst.data(), convRowPitch, 0, image));
2349
2350 return angle::Result::Continue;
2351}
